home assistant keybinds

mouse gestures:
https://github.com/jersou/mouse-actions/blob/main/examples/mouse-actions.json

right mouse + line down to open new tab
right mouse + line up to open anyrun
right mouse + line to left and right to focus-column-left and right
middle mouse + line to left and right to move-column-left and right
middle mouse + line up and down to workspace up and down
right mouse + draw c to close tab, reverse c to reopen
hold right mouse and scroll to switch tabs

maybe could do bindings with super modifier since thats on mouse?

close window, move left and right window

    # Bracket keys, comma and period to consume or expel windows
    "Mod+BracketLeft".action = consume-or-expel-window-left;
    "Mod+BracketRight".action = consume-or-expel-window-right;
    "Mod+Comma".action = consume-window-into-column;
    "Mod+Period".action = expel-window-from-column;

    # R to switch window widths, shift to switch window heights, control to reset
    "Mod+R".action = switch-preset-column-width;
    "Mod+Shift+R".action = switch-preset-window-height;
    "Mod+Ctrl+R".action = reset-window-height;

    # F to maximize, shift F to fullscreen, C to center
    "Mod+F".action = maximize-column;
    "Mod+Shift+F".action = fullscreen-window;
    "Mod+C".action = center-column;
